    <item>
      <title>Create a swarm</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/create-swarm/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/create-swarm/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;After you complete the &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/&#34;&gt;tutorial setup&lt;/a&gt; steps, you&#39;re ready&#xA;to create a swarm. Make sure the Docker Engine daemon is started on the host&#xA;machines.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open a terminal and ssh into the machine where you want to run your manager&#xA;node. This tutorial uses a machine named &lt;code&gt;manager1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Run the following command to create a new swarm:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div data-pagefind-ignore class=&#34;scroll-mt-20&#34; x-data x-ref=&#34;root&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;group relative&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;button x-data=&#34;{ code: &#39;JCBkb2NrZXIgc3dhcm0gaW5pdCAtLWFkdmVydGlzZS1hZGRyIDxNQU5BR0VSLUlQPg==&#39;, copying: false }&#34;&#xA;      class=&#34;absolute right-3 top-3 z-10 text-gray-light-300 dark:text-gray-dark-600&#34; title=&#34;copy&#34; @click=&#34;window.navigator.clipboard.writeText(atob(code).replaceAll(/^[\$&gt;]\s+/gm, &#39;&#39;));&#xA;      copying = true;&#xA;      setTimeout(() =&gt; copying = false, 2000);&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : !copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M300-200q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-560q0-24 18-42t42-18h440q24 0 42 18t18 42v560q0 24-18 42t-42 18H300ZM180-80q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-590q0-13 8.5-21.5T150-760q13 0 21.5 8.5T180-730v590h470q13 0 21.5 8.5T680-110q0 13-8.5 21.5T650-80H180Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;m421-389-98-98q-9-9-22-9t-23 10q-9 9-9 22t9 22l122 123q9 9 21 9t21-9l239-239q10-10 10-23t-10-23q-10-9-23.5-8.5T635-603L421-389Zm59 309q-82 0-155-31.5t-127.5-86Q143-252 111.5-325T80-480q0-83 31.5-156t86-127Q252-817 325-848.5T480-880q83 0 156 31.5T763-763q54 54 85.5 127T880-480q0 82-31.5 155T763-197.5q-54 54.5-127 86T480-80Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/button&gt;&#xA;     &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;syntax-light dark:syntax-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;gp&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; docker swarm init --advertise-addr &amp;lt;MANAGER-IP&amp;gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In the tutorial, the following command creates a swarm on the &lt;code&gt;manager1&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;machine:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Add nodes to the swarm</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/add-nodes/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/add-nodes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Once you&#39;ve &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/create-swarm/&#34;&gt;created a swarm&lt;/a&gt; with a manager node, you&#39;re ready&#xA;to add worker nodes.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open a terminal and ssh into the machine where you want to run a worker node.&#xA;This tutorial uses the name &lt;code&gt;worker1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Run the command produced by the &lt;code&gt;docker swarm init&lt;/code&gt; output from the&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/create-swarm/&#34;&gt;Create a swarm&lt;/a&gt; tutorial step to create a worker node&#xA;joined to the existing swarm:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div data-pagefind-ignore class=&#34;scroll-mt-20&#34; x-data x-ref=&#34;root&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;group relative&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;button x-data=&#34;{ code: &#39;JCBkb2NrZXIgc3dhcm0gam9pbiBcCiAgLS10b2tlbiAgU1dNVEtOLTEtNDluajFjbXFsMGprejVzOTU0eWkzb2V4M25lZHl6MGZiMHh4MTRpZTM5dHJ0aTR3eHYtOHZ4djhyc3Ntazc0M29qbndhY3JyMmU3YyBcCiAgMTkyLjE2OC45OS4xMDA6MjM3NwoKVGhpcyBub2RlIGpvaW5lZCBhIHN3YXJtIGFzIGEgd29ya2VyLg==&#39;, copying: false }&#34;&#xA;      class=&#34;absolute right-3 top-3 z-10 text-gray-light-300 dark:text-gray-dark-600&#34; title=&#34;copy&#34; @click=&#34;window.navigator.clipboard.writeText(atob(code).replaceAll(/^[\$&gt;]\s+/gm, &#39;&#39;));&#xA;      copying = true;&#xA;      setTimeout(() =&gt; copying = false, 2000);&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : !copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M300-200q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-560q0-24 18-42t42-18h440q24 0 42 18t18 42v560q0 24-18 42t-42 18H300ZM180-80q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-590q0-13 8.5-21.5T150-760q13 0 21.5 8.5T180-730v590h470q13 0 21.5 8.5T680-110q0 13-8.5 21.5T650-80H180Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;m421-389-98-98q-9-9-22-9t-23 10q-9 9-9 22t9 22l122 123q9 9 21 9t21-9l239-239q10-10 10-23t-10-23q-10-9-23.5-8.5T635-603L421-389Zm59 309q-82 0-155-31.5t-127.5-86Q143-252 111.5-325T80-480q0-83 31.5-156t86-127Q252-817 325-848.5T480-880q83 0 156 31.5T763-763q54 54 85.5 127T880-480q0 82-31.5 155T763-197.5q-54 54.5-127 86T480-80Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/button&gt;&#xA;     &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;syntax-light dark:syntax-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;gp&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; docker swarm join &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;  --token  SWMTKN-1-49nj1cmql0jkz5s954yi3oex3nedyz0fb0xx14ie39trti4wxv-8vxv8rssmk743ojnwacrr2e7c \&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;  192.168.99.100:2377&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;This node joined a swarm as a worker.&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you don&#39;t have the command available, you can run the following command&#xA;on a manager node to retrieve the join command for a worker:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Deploy a service to the swarm</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/deploy-service/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/deploy-service/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;After you &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/create-swarm/&#34;&gt;create a swarm&lt;/a&gt;, you can deploy a service to the&#xA;swarm. For this tutorial, you also &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/add-nodes/&#34;&gt;added worker nodes&lt;/a&gt;, but that&#xA;is not a requirement to deploy a service.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open a terminal and ssh into the machine where you run your manager node.&#xA;For example, the tutorial uses a machine named &lt;code&gt;manager1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Run the following command:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div data-pagefind-ignore class=&#34;scroll-mt-20&#34; x-data x-ref=&#34;root&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;group relative&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;button x-data=&#34;{ code: &#39;JCBkb2NrZXIgc2VydmljZSBjcmVhdGUgLS1yZXBsaWNhcyAxIC0tbmFtZSBoZWxsb3dvcmxkIGFscGluZSBwaW5nIGRvY2tlci5jb20KCjl1azQ2MzlxcGc3bnB3ZjNmbjJhYXNrc3I=&#39;, copying: false }&#34;&#xA;      class=&#34;absolute right-3 top-3 z-10 text-gray-light-300 dark:text-gray-dark-600&#34; title=&#34;copy&#34; @click=&#34;window.navigator.clipboard.writeText(atob(code).replaceAll(/^[\$&gt;]\s+/gm, &#39;&#39;));&#xA;      copying = true;&#xA;      setTimeout(() =&gt; copying = false, 2000);&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : !copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M300-200q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-560q0-24 18-42t42-18h440q24 0 42 18t18 42v560q0 24-18 42t-42 18H300ZM180-80q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-590q0-13 8.5-21.5T150-760q13 0 21.5 8.5T180-730v590h470q13 0 21.5 8.5T680-110q0 13-8.5 21.5T650-80H180Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;m421-389-98-98q-9-9-22-9t-23 10q-9 9-9 22t9 22l122 123q9 9 21 9t21-9l239-239q10-10 10-23t-10-23q-10-9-23.5-8.5T635-603L421-389Zm59 309q-82 0-155-31.5t-127.5-86Q143-252 111.5-325T80-480q0-83 31.5-156t86-127Q252-817 325-848.5T480-880q83 0 156 31.5T763-763q54 54 85.5 127T880-480q0 82-31.5 155T763-197.5q-54 54.5-127 86T480-80Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/button&gt;&#xA;     &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;syntax-light dark:syntax-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;gp&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; docker service create --replicas &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; --name helloworld alpine ping docker.com&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;9uk4639qpg7npwf3fn2aasksr&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;code&gt;docker service create&lt;/code&gt; command creates the service.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;code&gt;--name&lt;/code&gt; flag names the service &lt;code&gt;helloworld&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;code&gt;--replicas&lt;/code&gt; flag specifies the desired state of 1 running instance.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The arguments &lt;code&gt;alpine ping docker.com&lt;/code&gt; define the service as an Alpine&#xA;Linux container that executes the command &lt;code&gt;ping docker.com&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;docker service ls&lt;/code&gt; to see the list of running services:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Inspect a service on the swarm</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/inspect-service/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/inspect-service/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;When you have &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/deploy-service/&#34;&gt;deployed a service&lt;/a&gt; to your swarm, you can use&#xA;the Docker CLI to see details about the service running in the swarm.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you haven&#39;t already, open a terminal and ssh into the machine where you&#xA;run your manager node. For example, the tutorial uses a machine named&#xA;&lt;code&gt;manager1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;docker service inspect --pretty &amp;lt;SERVICE-ID&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; to display the details&#xA;about a service in an easily readable format.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To see the details on the &lt;code&gt;helloworld&lt;/code&gt; service:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Scale the service in the swarm</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/scale-service/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/scale-service/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Once you have &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/deploy-service/&#34;&gt;deployed a service&lt;/a&gt; to a swarm, you are ready&#xA;to use the Docker CLI to scale the number of containers in&#xA;the service. Containers running in a service are called tasks.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you haven&#39;t already, open a terminal and ssh into the machine where you&#xA;run your manager node. For example, the tutorial uses a machine named&#xA;&lt;code&gt;manager1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Run the following command to change the desired state of the&#xA;service running in the swarm:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Delete the service running on the swarm</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/delete-service/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/delete-service/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The remaining steps in the tutorial don&#39;t use the &lt;code&gt;helloworld&lt;/code&gt; service, so now&#xA;you can delete the service from the swarm.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you haven&#39;t already, open a terminal and ssh into the machine where you&#xA;run your manager node. For example, the tutorial uses a machine named&#xA;&lt;code&gt;manager1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;docker service rm helloworld&lt;/code&gt; to remove the &lt;code&gt;helloworld&lt;/code&gt; service.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div data-pagefind-ignore class=&#34;scroll-mt-20&#34; x-data x-ref=&#34;root&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;group relative&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;button x-data=&#34;{ code: &#39;JCBkb2NrZXIgc2VydmljZSBybSBoZWxsb3dvcmxkCgpoZWxsb3dvcmxk&#39;, copying: false }&#34;&#xA;      class=&#34;absolute right-3 top-3 z-10 text-gray-light-300 dark:text-gray-dark-600&#34; title=&#34;copy&#34; @click=&#34;window.navigator.clipboard.writeText(atob(code).replaceAll(/^[\$&gt;]\s+/gm, &#39;&#39;));&#xA;      copying = true;&#xA;      setTimeout(() =&gt; copying = false, 2000);&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : !copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M300-200q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-560q0-24 18-42t42-18h440q24 0 42 18t18 42v560q0 24-18 42t-42 18H300ZM180-80q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-590q0-13 8.5-21.5T150-760q13 0 21.5 8.5T180-730v590h470q13 0 21.5 8.5T680-110q0 13-8.5 21.5T650-80H180Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;m421-389-98-98q-9-9-22-9t-23 10q-9 9-9 22t9 22l122 123q9 9 21 9t21-9l239-239q10-10 10-23t-10-23q-10-9-23.5-8.5T635-603L421-389Zm59 309q-82 0-155-31.5t-127.5-86Q143-252 111.5-325T80-480q0-83 31.5-156t86-127Q252-817 325-848.5T480-880q83 0 156 31.5T763-763q54 54 85.5 127T880-480q0 82-31.5 155T763-197.5q-54 54.5-127 86T480-80Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/button&gt;&#xA;     &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;syntax-light dark:syntax-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;gp&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; docker service rm helloworld&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;helloworld&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;docker service inspect &amp;lt;SERVICE-ID&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; to verify that the swarm manager&#xA;removed the service. The CLI returns a message that the service is not&#xA;found:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Apply rolling updates to a service</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/rolling-update/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/rolling-update/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In a previous step of the tutorial, you &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/scale-service/&#34;&gt;scaled&lt;/a&gt; the number of&#xA;instances of a service. In this part of the tutorial, you deploy a service based&#xA;on the Redis 7.4.0 container tag. Then you upgrade the service to use the&#xA;Redis 7.4.1 container image using rolling updates.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you haven&#39;t already, open a terminal and ssh into the machine where you&#xA;run your manager node. For example, the tutorial uses a machine named&#xA;&lt;code&gt;manager1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Drain a node on the swarm</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/drain-node/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/swarm/swarm-tutorial/drain-node/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In earlier steps of the tutorial, all the nodes have been running with &lt;code&gt;Active&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;availability. The swarm manager can assign tasks to any &lt;code&gt;Active&lt;/code&gt; node, so up to&#xA;now all nodes have been available to receive tasks.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Sometimes, such as planned maintenance times, you need to set a node to &lt;code&gt;Drain&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;availability. &lt;code&gt;Drain&lt;/code&gt; availability  prevents a node from receiving new tasks&#xA;from the swarm manager. It also means the manager stops tasks running on the&#xA;node and launches replica tasks on a node with &lt;code&gt;Active&lt;/code&gt; availability.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
